17. super Keyword

The super keyword refers to the immediate Parent Class object.

It is used to access Parent Class members.

Uses of super keyword

• Access Parent Class Variables
• Call Parent Class Methods
• Call Parent Class Constructor

---------------------------------------------------------

18. Access Parent Class Variable

Example

class Animal{

    String name = "Animal";

}

class Dog extends Animal{

    String name = "Dog";

    void display(){

        System.out.println(super.name);

    }

}

Output

Animal

---------------------------------------------------------

19. Call Parent Class Method

Example

class Animal{

    void eat(){

        System.out.println("Animal is Eating");

    }

}

class Dog extends Animal{

    void bark(){

        super.eat();

        System.out.println("Dog is Barking");

    }

}

Output

Animal is Eating

Dog is Barking

---------------------------------------------------------

20. Call Parent Class Constructor

The super() keyword is used to call the Parent Class constructor.

Syntax

super();

or

super(parameter);

Example

class Animal{

    Animal(String name){

        System.out.println(name);

    }

}

class Dog extends Animal{

    Dog(){

        super("Tommy");

    }

}

The super() statement must always be the FIRST statement
inside the Child Class constructor.

---------------------------------------------------------

21. Constructor Chaining

Constructor Chaining means calling one constructor from another.

Types

1. this()

Calls the current class constructor.

2. super()

Calls the Parent Class constructor.

Benefits

• Code Reusability

• Avoids Duplicate Initialization

• Cleaner Code

---------------------------------------------------------

22. this Keyword

The this keyword refers to the current object of the class.

Uses

• Refer Current Class Variable

• Call Current Class Method

• Call Current Class Constructor

• Pass Current Object

---------------------------------------------------------

23. Resolving Naming Conflict

Example

class Student{

    int id;

    Student(int id){

        this.id = id;

    }

}

Here

this.id

→ Instance Variable

id

→ Constructor Parameter

---------------------------------------------------------

24. Difference between this and super

this

• Refers to Current Class Object

• Access Current Class Members

• Calls Current Class Constructor

super

• Refers to Parent Class Object

• Access Parent Class Members

• Calls Parent Class Constructor

---------------------------------------------------------

25. Method Overriding

Method Overriding means redefining the Parent Class method
inside the Child Class.

Rules

• Method Name should be same.

• Parameters should be same.

• Return Type should be same.

• Happens only in Inheritance.

Example

class Animal{

    void sound(){

        System.out.println("Animal Sound");

    }

}

class Dog extends Animal{

    void sound(){

        System.out.println("Dog Barks");

    }

}

Output

Dog Barks

---------------------------------------------------------

26. instanceof Operator

instanceof is a binary operator.

It checks whether an object belongs to a particular class,
subclass or interface.

Syntax

object instanceof ClassName

Returns

true

or

false

---------------------------------------------------------

Example

Dog d = new Dog();

System.out.println(d instanceof Dog);

Output

true

---------------------------------------------------------

Example

System.out.println(d instanceof Animal);

Output

true

Reason

Dog inherits Animal.

---------------------------------------------------------

Example

Circle c = new Circle();

System.out.println(c instanceof Triangle);

Output

false

Reason

Circle object does not belong to Triangle class.

---------------------------------------------------------

27. Upcasting

Parent p = new Child();

Example

Animal a = new Dog();

Valid

Reason

Dog IS-A Animal.

---------------------------------------------------------

28. Downcasting

Dog d = new Animal();

Invalid

Compile Time Error

Reason

Parent object cannot be directly assigned to Child reference.

